<br>
wpn, cd, parry<br>
<br>
or <br>
<br>
wpn, shield, parry<br>
<br>
But a combination isnt an option at the moment. RvR fights are so fast you dont have the time to grab in you backpack and swap items. Sad that mythic never looked serious at this. But there more things like mythic doesnt care for bm. Like giving RA Avoid Pain. Why beserkers (light tank can spec this RA) and mercenaries and blademaster cant <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START >: --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/mad.gif ALT=">:"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#c0c0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=xrian>xrian</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Initiate</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#000000>(8/28/03 10:57 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=125.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> bm spec to try</span><hr size=1> I am probably the only one with the spec I chose. But so far it has been working rather well.<br>
<br>
I am: 49pierce, 42shield, 40parry, and like 6cd.(with an additional +12 to everything from sc'd stuff)<br>
<br>
If I duel using pierce and shield, I don't stand a chance, it seems my guy doesn't want to block much. However if I duel with 2 piercers, I do rather well, against any other tank. <br>
If I head to RvR, I toss the shield up and lay out the slams like there's no tomorrow. If you keep your inventory screen open while you are fighting, it does not take that long to toggle between the shield and offhand. Just lower the opacity so you can see through the box, and you're good to go. <br>
<br>
I'd like to know if anyone else has this spec and what they think.<br>
<br>
Thanks<br>
